9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 686, L.D. 1768, “An Act to Protect
10 Residents of Mobile Home Parks by Amending the Real Estate Transfer Tax”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §4852, sub-§2, ¶A, as repealed and replaced by PL 1989, c.
13 48, §§5 and 31, is amended by amending subparagraph (5) to read:
14 (5) Pay the administrative costs of state public bodies or other public
15 instrumentalities and private, nonprofit corporations directly associated with
16 housing projects; and
17 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §4852, sub-§2, ¶A, as repealed and replaced by PL 1989, c.
18 48, §§5 and 31, is amended by enacting a new subparagraph (5-A) to read:
19 (5-A) Maintain housing affordability in mobile home parks to support ownership
20 of mobile home parks by mobile home owner's associations, resident-owned
21 housing cooperatives or other nonprofit entities representing the interests of mobile
22 home owners in mobile home parks; and'
23 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 4 and inserting the following:
24 'Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §4641-C, sub-§22 is enacted to read:
25 22. Certain deeds of mobile home park. Deeds conveying ownership of a mobile
26 home park from its owner to a majority of residents of the park at the time of conveyance
27 who are residents of the State or a mobile home owners' association of the mobile home
28 park organized in this State when the conveyance is made pursuant to Title 10, section
29 9094-A.
30 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
31 allocations are made.
