9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, removes the bill's
1111 provision requiring the real estate transfer tax received by the State from buyers of mobile
1122 home parks be allocated entirely to the Housing Opportunities for Maine Fund within the
1133 Maine State Housing Authority. The amendment adds a provision modifying the purposes
1144 of the Housing Opportunities for Maine Program to include maintaining housing
1155 affordability in mobile home parks to support ownership of mobile home owner's
1166 associations, resident-owned housing cooperatives or other nonprofit entities representing
1177 the interests of mobile home owners in mobile home parks.
1188 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
